## ğŸ“Œ Project Overview

- **Type:** Mobile App
- **Role:** UI/UX Designer
- **Tools Used:** Figma, Google Fonts, Design Tokens
- **Approach:** Behavior-Driven UX, Empathy-Focused Design

---

## ğŸ¯ Problem Statement

Most AI chatbots lack emotional depth and habit apps focus only on streaks. ChitChat fills the gap by offering a safe space for casual, uplifting, and creative conversations driven by emotional well-being.

---

## ğŸ‘¥ Target Users

- People feeling lonely or emotionally low
- Users seeking casual companionship or creative support
- Young adults, remote workers, freelancers

---

## ğŸ§  UX Goals

- Design emotionally engaging AI interactions
- Build habit-forming flows using behavioral psychology
- Keep the experience minimal, warm, and intuitive

---

## ğŸ› ï¸ Core Features

- AI chat with tone customization
- Daily mood-based conversation triggers
- Progress journal for saved chats and ideas

---

## ğŸ§ª Process & Methods

- Applied BJ Foggâ€™s Behavior Model & Atomic Habits concepts
- Created low-to-high fidelity wireframes in Figma
- Developed 3 core flows: Add Prompt, Daily Check-in, View Progress
- Conducted user feedback rounds and iterative design updates

---

## ğŸ¨ Visual Design

- Soft color palette (Bule, White)
- Rounded typography for approachability
- Accessible layout and dark mode support

---

## âœ… Key Takeaways

- Designing for emotion = empathy + tone, not just visuals
- Behavior science improves UX retention
- Simplicity wins over feature-heavy interfaces
- Design systems boost speed and consistency
- Feedback is critical for human-like AI design

